==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Binervate
<hw>Bi*nerv"ate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bis</ets> twice + <ets>nervus</ets> sinew, nerve.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Two-nerved; -- applied to leaves
which have two longitudinal ribs or nerves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having only two nerves, as the
wings of some insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bing</ent>⟦br⟧
